@xilllllix it is true. BUT learning html & css first won’t help you to learn JS easier. You can perfectly teach those topics the other way around (like this course) and won’t affect anything. Or on the contrary, like Kyle says, you will find html & css super easy. 

And, even though I love styles and make something look pretty, I recognize that the functionality is the most important thing to learn. I usually make basic elements, add the functionality and then take my time to make it look beautiful and give a good user experience.

But that’s just my opinion, everyone learn in different ways. If you find it easier like you say, it is okay. 👌🏾
